WEBVTT

02:35.192 --> 02:38.182
Excuse me, but aren't
you Sarah Morton?

02:40.959 --> 02:43.755
It is you.
I recognize you.

02:43.825 --> 02:47.315
Look, I'm reading
your latest novel.

02:47.392 --> 02:49.585
I love it.

02:49.658 --> 02:52.989
I'm a big fan of Inspector Dorwell.
I've read all your books--

02:53.059 --> 02:56.151
<i>You must have mistaken me
with someone else.</i>

02:56.226 --> 03:00.057
I'm not the person
you think I am.
Excuse me.

03:08.125 --> 03:11.058
<i>♪♪ [Rock]</i>

03:20.226 --> 03:23.954
Excuse me.
Good morning.
What would you like?

03:24.025 --> 03:25.958
- Whiskey, please.
- Ice?

03:26.025 --> 03:28.015
Yes.

03:31.525 --> 03:34.118
<i>[Woman]
Yeah, and after that
in all the directories.</i>

03:34.192 --> 03:38.887
<i>And we will renew, most definitely.
That shouldn't be a problem.</i>

03:38.959 --> 03:41.188
Just a minute.
Hello, Sarah. How are you?

03:41.259 --> 03:44.420
- Could be better.
Is John in?
- Yes, but he's in a meeting.

03:44.492 --> 03:46.651
Who with?

03:46.725 --> 03:49.352
- Terry Long.
- Who?

03:49.426 --> 03:51.619
Uh, just--

03:53.492 --> 03:58.289
Yeah. I'm in the process
of drawing up the contract now
and it should be with you shortly.

03:58.359 --> 04:00.621
- Yeah, I'm absolutely sure.
<i>- [Door Opens]</i>

04:00.692 --> 04:03.023
Now, you're on
what's called "a roll."

04:03.092 --> 04:07.355
You must keep the momentum
going. Take a short holiday,
but nothing too long.

04:07.426 --> 04:09.450
Sarah.

04:09.525 --> 04:13.822
Um, let me introduce you.
Sarah Morton, Terry Long.
Terry Long, Sarah Morton.

04:13.892 --> 04:18.257
I'm so pleased to meet you.
My mother adores you.
She's read all your Dorwell books.

04:18.326 --> 04:22.884
[Chuckles]
Right. Well, Terry,
always a pleasure.

04:22.959 --> 04:25.721
We'll speak very soon.
And congratulations again
on that award.

04:25.792 --> 04:28.385
- I'm sure it's the first of many.
- Oh, geez, John.

04:28.459 --> 04:30.618
Very nice to have met you.

04:30.692 --> 04:34.750
And do hurry. My mother's
impatiently awaiting the arrival
of the newest Inspector Dorwell book.

04:36.959 --> 04:39.256
So what award
did that little shit get?

04:39.326 --> 04:42.293
The Manchester Book Critics.

04:42.359 --> 04:46.689
Hardly the Booker Prize, I know,
but it's not bad for a first novel.

04:46.758 --> 04:50.157
The "little shit," as you call him,
has talent.

04:50.226 --> 04:52.352
I just hope he sells.

04:52.426 --> 04:55.551
- I trust you taught him
your favourite motto.
- And what motto's that?

04:55.625 --> 04:58.615
You know damn well.
You drilled it into me
20 years ago.

04:58.692 --> 05:02.421
"Awards are like haemorrhoids.
Sooner or later every asshole gets one."

05:02.491 --> 05:05.152
[Chuckles]
Did I say that?

05:06.792 --> 05:09.282
My God, you're jealous,
aren't you?

05:10.925 --> 05:13.358
You don't look after me anymore.

05:13.425 --> 05:17.950
<i>Just because I give a little fledgling
some encouragement does not mean
that I am neglecting you.</i>

05:18.025 --> 05:23.424
Besides, you've never had
any problems finding inspiration
for the Dorwell series.

05:23.491 --> 05:27.016
You write with such remarkable ease
I wonder you need me at all.

05:33.792 --> 05:36.782
Okay, Sarah, what's the matter?

05:38.226 --> 05:40.715
<i>Can't be money.
You're rolling in it.</i>

05:40.792 --> 05:44.884
It's incredible. The only thing
you can find to talk about
to me is money.

05:46.625 --> 05:48.649
<i>I don't give a damn about money...</i>

05:48.725 --> 05:50.954
or success!

05:51.025 --> 05:54.288
- I just want to find--
- An inspiring plot.

05:54.359 --> 05:57.087
<i>[Sighs]
No. You don't understand.</i>

05:57.159 --> 06:01.115
It's--It's got nothing
to do with inspiration.

06:01.192 --> 06:04.647
I'm--I'm fed up with murders...

06:04.725 --> 06:06.988
<i>and investigations.</i>

06:07.059 --> 06:10.492
Why don't you confound your critics
and write something completely different?

06:10.558 --> 06:13.650
Put Dorwell on the shelf,
as it were.

06:13.725 --> 06:17.385
You didn't like the last one, did you?
I knew it! And you haven't had
the balls to tell me.

06:17.458 --> 06:21.550
That's simply not true.
You know very well I've loved
the Dorwell series right from the beginning.

06:21.625 --> 06:24.956
As well you might...
considering the money they make you.

06:26.192 --> 06:28.318
[Clicks Tongue, Sighs]

06:36.992 --> 06:39.050
Do you like France?

06:40.892 --> 06:42.825
I like frogs' legs.

06:42.892 --> 06:45.358
<i>So what?</i>

06:45.425 --> 06:47.688
My house.

06:47.758 --> 06:51.919
Why don't you go there
for a while, hmm?
Breathe some fresh air.

06:51.992 --> 06:55.948
It's free, it's out of season,
the weather's glorious.
There's a swimming pool.

06:56.025 --> 06:58.288
Would you come and visit me?

06:58.358 --> 07:01.019
<i>Well, I have got my daughter.</i>

07:02.092 --> 07:04.456
<i>But maybe I'll come
for a weekend.</i>

09:07.125 --> 09:08.785
[French]
- Are you Marcel?
- Yes.

09:08.858 --> 09:10.825
Hello, I'm Sarah Morton.

09:10.892 --> 09:12.950
- How was your trip?
- Very nice.

09:13.025 --> 09:14.992
- May I carry this?
- It's on wheels.

09:15.059 --> 09:17.992
- I'll take the small one.
- Thank you.

09:18.059 --> 09:20.049
My car is just outside.

09:20.125 --> 09:22.115
Okay.

10:15.391 --> 10:17.722
[French]
The bedrooms and bath are upstairs,

10:17.792 --> 10:20.588
the kitchen's on the left.

10:20.658 --> 10:23.625
I'll let you take a look around.

10:23.692 --> 10:26.249
I turned on the hot water and gas.

10:27.992 --> 10:31.356
If you need anything,
you've got my number?

10:31.425 --> 10:34.620
- Yes, John gave it to me.
- Good.

10:34.692 --> 10:36.591
To go to the village,

10:36.658 --> 10:39.648
you can take the footpath I showed you...

10:39.725 --> 10:42.590
or use the moped in the garage.

10:42.658 --> 10:44.989
The keys are in the ignition.

10:45.059 --> 10:47.083
Thank you, Marcel. Goodbye.

10:47.158 --> 10:49.455
Goodbye, madame.
Enjoy your rest.

11:34.225 --> 11:36.215
[Sighs]

14:08.924 --> 14:11.221
<i>- Bonjour.
- Bonjour.</i>

14:11.291 --> 14:13.690
[French]
What can I get for you?

14:13.758 --> 14:16.486
- Um--
- An aperitif?

14:16.558 --> 14:18.548
No.

14:18.625 --> 14:21.421
Uh, maybe something lighter?

14:21.491 --> 14:23.390
How about a panaché?

14:24.391 --> 14:27.790
No.Just a cup of tea.

14:27.858 --> 14:30.324
Very well.

15:00.225 --> 15:03.522
<i>[Woman On TV Speaking French]
In Marseilles, bus service
is drastically reduced,</i>

15:03.592 --> 15:06.582
<i>but the Metro is running at 75%.</i>

15:06.658 --> 15:09.386
<i>It's the second strike in two weeks...</i>

15:09.458 --> 15:11.822
<i>and passengers are growing weary--</i>

15:11.891 --> 15:14.881
<i>[Channels Changing]</i>

15:18.325 --> 15:21.315
[Line Ringing]

15:21.391 --> 15:24.085
- [Man Speaking English] Hello?
- Hello, Father. It's me.

15:24.158 --> 15:28.421
- Are you all right?
- Yes, I've arrived safely.

15:28.491 --> 15:31.821
- How is the house?
- The house is lovely.

15:31.891 --> 15:34.552
- The weather?
- The weather's gorgeous.

15:34.625 --> 15:38.752
- How is the weather in London?
- Doesn't stop raining.

15:38.824 --> 15:40.655
- Are you all right?
- Yes, I'm okay.

15:40.725 --> 15:43.521
- Have you met anyone?
- No, I haven't seen anyone.

15:43.592 --> 15:46.820
You shouldn't stay by yourself.
Try to get out.

15:46.891 --> 15:49.085
- Father. Yeah--
- [Muttering]

15:49.158 --> 15:52.751
Look, Father, if there's
a problem of any kind,
ask Mrs. Smith for help.

15:52.824 --> 15:55.155
- All right?
- I don't need anyone's help.

15:55.225 --> 15:57.556
Yes. You take care now.

15:57.625 --> 15:59.818
- You too.
- All right. Bye-bye.

15:59.891 --> 16:02.051
Goodbye.

16:27.291 --> 16:29.281
[Clears Throat]

16:45.991 --> 16:47.981
[Exhales Sharply]

17:42.425 --> 17:45.415
<i>[Birds Twittering]</i>

18:45.958 --> 18:48.118
[Ringing]

18:48.191 --> 18:50.124
- Hello?
- [John] Sarah!

18:50.191 --> 18:52.420
- John, how are you?
- I'm very well.

18:52.491 --> 18:55.253
- I should be asking you
that question.
- [Chuckles]

18:55.325 --> 18:58.883
So, tell me,
how's everything going, darling?
Did Marcel come and fetch you?

18:58.958 --> 19:02.891
Yes, but listen. I have just
one thing to say to you,
and that's thank you.

19:02.958 --> 19:06.755
You were right, as usual.
Your house is a little piece
of paradise.

19:06.824 --> 19:09.553
- And I've already begun working.
- Hmm? So soon?

19:09.624 --> 19:12.989
Yes. The idea kept running
through my mind
while I was on the train.

19:13.058 --> 19:16.457
- You know, one of those stupid things
that just latch on and won't let go.
- Really?

19:16.525 --> 19:20.753
- I don't know where
it's heading, but--
- So, what's Dorwell up to now?

19:20.824 --> 19:23.291
- Well, I'm not ready
to talk about it right now.
- All right.

19:23.358 --> 19:27.223
But I think it might be quite funny.
Anyway, I'm going to wait
until I'm sure.

19:27.291 --> 19:30.315
Well, that's marvellous.
Well, I'm glad you're happy.

19:30.391 --> 19:32.619
Have you been out
and about yet?

19:32.691 --> 19:36.216
- No. I'm just enjoying
the peace and quiet here.
- Good.

19:36.291 --> 19:39.655
Yeah. So, when are you
thinking of coming?

19:39.724 --> 19:42.987
Um, I don't know.

19:43.058 --> 19:46.752
I'm not sure.
It--It depends on the work,
you know.

19:46.824 --> 19:51.019
Um, look, I'm sorry, sweetheart.
I've got another call
coming through.

19:51.091 --> 19:55.990
Now, you take care,
and call me when you're ready
to read me something, all right?

19:57.624 --> 19:59.489
- Right.
- Fine.

19:59.557 --> 20:01.615
Goodbye, John.

20:13.757 --> 20:15.747
[Sighs]

20:22.624 --> 20:24.614
[Exhales]

20:37.124 --> 20:40.114
<i>[Car Approaching]</i>

20:42.124 --> 20:44.114
[Gasps]

20:47.391 --> 20:49.721
<i>[Car Door Closes]</i>

21:03.924 --> 21:05.857
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

21:05.924 --> 21:09.153
<i>- [Keys Jangling]
- [Rustling]</i>

21:11.458 --> 21:13.049
[Gasps]

21:13.124 --> 21:14.613
[French]
You scared me!

21:14.691 --> 21:17.988
Who are you?
What are you doing in my house?

21:18.058 --> 21:20.820
Your house? This is my house!

21:20.891 --> 21:23.051
I should be asking you.

21:26.325 --> 21:29.053
<i>- [English]
Are you English?</i>
- That's correct.

21:29.124 --> 21:33.955
I'm Sarah Morton. I'm a writer.
And my publisher, John Bosload,
is letting me this house.

21:34.024 --> 21:37.787
Ah. So you're Daddy's
latest conquest.

21:39.124 --> 21:41.091
You're his daughter?

21:41.158 --> 21:43.989
So what? Didn't he warn you?

21:44.058 --> 21:48.424
- No, he didn't tell me
you'd be coming.
<i>- [Chuckles]</i>

21:48.490 --> 21:50.889
I'm not surprised. Is he here?

21:50.958 --> 21:53.686
<i>No, I'm here on my own,
and I'm here to work.</i>

21:53.757 --> 21:55.690
<i>Maybe he'll come
and visit.</i>

21:55.757 --> 21:57.883
I'm glad he's not here.

21:59.191 --> 22:01.783
Are you going to be staying long?

22:01.857 --> 22:06.415
I don't know.
I don't have much work these days.

22:06.490 --> 22:08.719
So, which bedroom did you take?

22:08.791 --> 22:11.815
- The one upstairs
overlooking the pool.
<i>- Of course.</i>

22:11.891 --> 22:15.881
That's the best one.
Well, I'm gonna unpack.

22:17.724 --> 22:19.714
Sorry.

22:27.824 --> 22:29.791
[Line Ringing]

22:29.857 --> 22:32.824
[John On Answering Machine]
Hello. Leave your name, number
and any message you might have...

22:32.891 --> 22:35.017
and I'll get right back to you.

22:35.091 --> 22:38.546
[Whispering]
Bastard! You could have told me your
daughter was coming to your bloody house.

22:38.624 --> 22:40.682
How do you expect me
to work now?

22:40.757 --> 22:43.485
- It's Sarah. Goodbye.
- [Clears Throat]

22:45.490 --> 22:49.254
- I couldn't get through to London.
<i>- Is there anything to eat?</i>

22:49.325 --> 22:52.087
Yes. Go and look for it
in the kitchen.

22:52.158 --> 22:55.852
Personally, I'm gonna go back to bed.
I have to work early in the morning.

22:55.924 --> 23:00.153
Fine. Good night.
Sarah, right?

23:00.225 --> 23:02.384
Right.

23:02.457 --> 23:04.447
I'm Julie.

23:39.857 --> 23:42.847
<i>[Water Running]</i>

25:29.591 --> 25:31.581
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

26:02.324 --> 26:05.314
- [Printer Whirring]
<i>- [Water Splashing]</i>

27:14.857 --> 27:16.824
You're not too hot?

27:18.958 --> 27:20.891
- [Gasps]
- Sorry. I woke you up.

27:20.958 --> 27:24.391
No. I was just dozing.

27:24.457 --> 27:26.947
[Chuckles]
You must be working too hard.

27:27.024 --> 27:31.082
You should have a swim in the pool.
The water's cold. It'll wake you up.

27:31.157 --> 27:34.613
Well, thank you for your advice,
but I absolutely loathe swimming pools.

27:35.991 --> 27:38.514
Yeah, I know what you mean.

27:38.591 --> 27:40.956
I prefer the sea too.

27:41.024 --> 27:44.752
The ocean.
The crashing waves.

27:44.824 --> 27:49.655
<i>The feeling of danger,
that you could lose footing at any time
and be swept away.</i>

27:49.724 --> 27:51.714
Pools are boring.

27:51.791 --> 27:54.758
There's no excitement, no--

27:54.824 --> 27:56.950
no feeling of infinity.

27:57.024 --> 27:59.115
<i>- It's just a big bathtub.</i>
- [Clears Throat]

27:59.190 --> 28:01.487
It's more like a cesspool
of living bacteria.

28:01.557 --> 28:05.820
Oh, that? No, it's just a bit
of dirt and leaves.

28:09.257 --> 28:13.213
<i>So, what are you writing?
A romance novel?</i>

28:13.290 --> 28:16.587
[Scoffs]
God, no. I write crime fiction.

28:16.657 --> 28:20.784
<i>Oh, yeah. That's how
he makes his money.</i>

28:20.857 --> 28:25.222
And that's how he can afford to buy
a beautiful house in France
for his daughter to enjoy.

28:30.490 --> 28:33.787
What about you?
Are your books selling well?

28:33.857 --> 28:37.312
- I can't complain.
- What is this one about?

28:37.390 --> 28:39.823
Murders and
a police investigation.

28:39.891 --> 28:44.085
[Chuckles]
In the Lubéron
with rich English tourists.

28:44.157 --> 28:46.818
Listen, if you don't mind,
I do have work to do.

28:46.891 --> 28:49.153
Okay. I leave you alone,
Miss Marple.

28:49.224 --> 28:52.487
<i>I need to make
some phone calls anyway.</i>

29:02.357 --> 29:05.722
[Julie Speaking French]
He was at the Macumba?

29:05.791 --> 29:07.758
[Laughs]
No way!

29:07.824 --> 29:09.814
With Jean-Pierre?

29:12.724 --> 29:14.986
Yeah, right.

29:15.057 --> 29:17.388
What a pervert!
[Laughs]

29:19.924 --> 29:21.914
You're gross!

29:22.757 --> 29:24.747
He came back?

29:27.190 --> 29:29.282
I don't know.

29:34.524 --> 29:37.821
- [English] Going shopping?
- No, I'm going to have lunch
in the village.

29:37.891 --> 29:39.915
Ah, good idea.

29:39.990 --> 29:43.719
By the way, I spoke to Marcel.
He's coming very soon
for the pool.

29:47.990 --> 29:49.855
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

29:49.924 --> 29:52.584
[French]
His English bitch
has a broomstick up her butt.

30:16.957 --> 30:19.947
<i>[Bell Tolls Twice]</i>

30:29.157 --> 30:32.886
[French]
- May I have the bill? Please.
- Yes.

31:04.390 --> 31:06.755
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

31:06.824 --> 31:10.950
<i>[Julie, English]
Hello? Don't worry about it.</i>

31:11.023 --> 31:14.184
I'm not going to bother her.
Anyway, it's a big house.

31:18.490 --> 31:20.514
Did you ring Mom?

31:21.591 --> 31:25.115
I'm telling you,
she's still waiting, so hurry up.

31:26.457 --> 31:29.253
Yes, <i>c'est ça. Ciao.</i>

31:29.324 --> 31:31.348
It's your publisher.

31:34.657 --> 31:37.214
John? Hello? John?

31:38.224 --> 31:40.214
He hung up.

31:45.591 --> 31:47.581
[Line Ringing]

31:49.324 --> 31:52.950
- [Woman] Hello?
- Hello, this is Sarah Morton.
Could I speak to John, please?

31:53.023 --> 31:56.388
- He's gone out.
- Oh. Really?

31:56.457 --> 31:59.583
- Well, could you ask him
to call me back in France?
- Okay then.

31:59.657 --> 32:02.146
Yes, thank you. Goodbye.

32:04.057 --> 32:07.252
He scolded me.
He told me not to bother you.

32:07.324 --> 32:09.984
He said I should leave you alone
so you could work.

32:11.757 --> 32:13.814
Listen, Julie.
I'm going to be frank with you.

32:13.890 --> 32:16.722
I need peace and quiet
to concentrate.

32:16.791 --> 32:18.724
And since we share
the same living space,

32:18.791 --> 32:23.417
I must ask you just to go about
your business without getting
in the way of mine, hmm?

32:23.490 --> 32:27.218
I mean, this house is certainly
big enough for the two of us.
So, please make an effort.

32:27.290 --> 32:29.984
I was only trying to be polite
and make friends.

32:30.057 --> 32:32.752
- But if you prefer I don't--
- I don't prefer anything!

32:32.823 --> 32:36.813
I just want to work
on my book in peace.

32:36.890 --> 32:41.880
Fine. That's too bad, though,
because I just bought loads
of nice food.

32:41.957 --> 32:45.550
I guess I have to eat
my foie gras all alone.

33:04.157 --> 33:07.147
<i>[People Screaming On TV]</i>

33:27.390 --> 33:29.721
<i>[Car Engine Starts]</i>

33:32.390 --> 33:35.380
<i>[Car Driving A way]</i>

34:59.290 --> 35:01.223
<i>Ça va?</i>

35:01.290 --> 35:04.621
[French]
- We're almost there.
- I'm wasted.

35:04.690 --> 35:06.089
Are you okay?

35:06.157 --> 35:08.283
- Where are we?
- My house.

35:08.357 --> 35:10.324
You live here?

35:10.390 --> 35:12.414
Yeah, I swear!

35:14.623 --> 35:16.557
[Shouts]

35:16.623 --> 35:19.613
<i>♪♪ [Dance Rock Playing Loudly]</i>

35:23.290 --> 35:25.223
[French]
Can't you turn the music up?

35:25.290 --> 35:27.722
No, the old bag's sleeping upstairs.

35:27.790 --> 35:29.780
[English]
Oh.

35:54.190 --> 35:56.884
[Giggling]

35:56.957 --> 35:59.947
[Both Moaning Softly]

36:15.123 --> 36:18.113
[Moaning Continues]

36:29.157 --> 36:32.147
<i>[Moaning Continues]</i>

36:40.756 --> 36:42.746
<i>[Moaning Stops]</i>

37:08.856 --> 37:10.618
[French]
Good morning.

37:11.190 --> 37:13.656
<i>Bonjour.</i>

37:13.723 --> 37:16.213
I made some coffee, if you like.

37:18.057 --> 37:20.047
<i>Oui.</i>

37:25.390 --> 37:27.515
I hope we weren't too loud?

37:28.656 --> 37:32.885
I don't speak French.
I can't understand a word.

37:32.957 --> 37:34.947
<i>Pardon.</i>

37:43.324 --> 37:45.654
[Whistling]

37:47.424 --> 37:49.788
[French Continues]
Get up!

37:49.856 --> 37:51.846
[Groans]

38:01.257 --> 38:03.450
I've got to get to work.

38:03.523 --> 38:05.252
Just a quickie.

38:05.324 --> 38:09.189
I'd love to, but I've really got to go.

38:09.257 --> 38:11.156
And there's that woman.

38:11.224 --> 38:14.020
- You saw her?
- Yeah, she's outside.

38:14.090 --> 38:16.284
- She's a foreigner?
- Yes.

38:16.357 --> 38:19.381
- English.
